snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a millennial but am tired of hearing others being so critical of older generations, boomers etc. Even if its supposedly in fun.
Some prob once felt the same way at the same age, just like you will one day will prob see things more like they do now. Time goes so quickly and life teaches in ways you'll never expect. Not one age is better than the other. We could be learning from the life experiences of those older than us while we have them instead of knocking them. They have seen a time in life we can only imagine or see through photos or stories. Every age can have something to offer, but not every person does. If our generation and that behind us keep this up, who will know what real care and respect are?
